# Panda skill tracking — session start (Claude Code)

When this is a **new agent chat** in Cursor (first assistant turn), **before** substantive work:

1. **Ask once** whether to start **Panda Skills** usage tracking for **Claude Code** (`auto_track_skill_usage.py` uses the **default Claude Code layout**: `~/.claude/projects` transcripts → `~/.claude/ai-tracking/skill-usage.jsonl`).
2. **Launchd**: if they use macOS auto-start, the plist label is **`com.panda.skills.claude-code`**. To enable after install: `launchctl bootstrap "gui/$(id -u)" "$HOME/Library/LaunchAgents/com.panda.skills.claude-code.plist"`. To check: `launchctl print "gui/$(id -u)/com.panda.skills.claude-code"` (errors may print to `~/.claude/ai-tracking/skill-tracker-launchd.err.log`). Avoid a **second** duplicate watcher writing the same JSONL.
3. **If they say yes**, run the watcher **in the background**. Resolve `--repo` from `git remote get-url origin` basename or the workspace folder name.
4. **Script path**: use `$PANDA_SKILLS_ROOT/scripts/auto_track_skill_usage.py` when set; otherwise locate `scripts/auto_track_skill_usage.py` under their Panda Skills checkout (ask once if unclear).
5. If they decline or tracking is already running, **do not** ask again in the same thread unless they ask.

Skip this prompt when the user’s first message already answers tracking (e.g. “start skill tracker”, “no tracker”).
